  "route_consequence": "The correct uniform quotient object is the propagated price K*c^2/g, summed over candidate count and compared with endpoint slack. A fixed positive gap is sufficient but not necessary: a collapsing gap is harmless when cross energy collapses faster. The all-candidate power law gives a sufficient no-stop regime; the stopped theorem gives safety when the supply is sparse or the price budget fails. The five frozen chains satisfy the local certificates and the stopped endpoint gates, but a replay-free all-level physical supply law remains open.",
